As the battle between ex-President Goodluck Jonathan and Governor Seriake Dickson’s camps on who to back as PDP candidate ahead of the Nov. 16 governorship election in Bayelsa rages, the Peoples Democratic Party Support Group (PDPSG) has urged the national leadership of the party to probe activities of the former Nigerian leader and his wife, Patience. The group, in a statement by its coordinator, Chief Isaac Ipidei, alleged that Jonathan’s role in the increasing number of aspirants must be investigated in the interest of the party. Ipidei said the large number of contenders was a deliberate design to cause confusion and make the PDP lose the governorship election. According to him, while Jonathan was allegedly encouraging many aspirants to buy PDP forms to contest, his wife and political ally, A. J. Turner were fraternising with a leader of the APC in the state. Jonathan, Dickson in titanic battle to install next Bayelsa governor 2015:15 Power Brokers In Aso Rock Sylva’s political battle: The Obasanjo factor Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin